The surest sign of a regime change is when it starts fighting the statues.
Americans understand this no worse than everyone else - hence the deliberately theatrical demolition of the statue of Saddam Hussein in Firdos Square in Baghdad in 2003.
Stephen Miller, one of the key ideologues of the Trump government, no doubt knew what he was doing when he raised a symbolic ax over the Statue of Liberty during a bitter dispute with CNN journalist Jim Acosta about the president&#39;s proposals to drastically reduce legal migration.
