Contrary to his custom, Limbaugh really hit the mark here.
The meaning of the statue depends solely on the angle of view.
Lazarus&#39; great creative achievement was to see her as the haggard, unhappy, but full of hope people would see her on the decks of ships after a long and often difficult voyage.
It means literally looking at the world through the eyes of people seeking refuge and a chance for a better life.
Her statue responds to them with the words of hope and hospitality they dream of hearing.
And, of course, this is not a perspective that Miller and Trump will ever want to acknowledge.
Their torch is needed not to light the way, but to kindle hatred, which is the only source of their power.
