How football&#39;s financial rules will affect Neymar&#39;s move to Paris
Rules aimed at preventing unlimited spending by European football clubs will not prevent Neymar&#39;s world-record transfer from Barcelona to France&#39;s Paris Saint-Germain.
Consequences of any kind could come down the chain for Paris Saint-Germain from UEFA, the governing body overseeing European football, which has the power to ban teams from participating in the prestigious Champions League.
From the financial fair play rules introduced by UEFA in 2011, PSG will eventually have to show that Neymar&#39;s transfer was funded without major losses.
