During the first wave of FFP sanctions in 2014, PSG as well as Abu Dhabi&#39;s Manchester City faced severe sanctions.
PSG was fined 60 million euros (at that rate it is 82 million dollars), which was later reduced to 20 million euros, and it was ordered to limit their squad in the Champions League during the 2014-1015 season to 21 players instead of the usual 25.
UEFA is monitoring clubs that may try to outsmart its financial inspectors by inflating their income at the expense of companies tied to the club&#39;s owners.
Although the Qatari company could have sponsored PSG, if the funding was deemed to exceed standard market rates, UEFA would not allow it to be considered legitimate income.
This is exactly what happened in 2014, when UEFA ruled that the amount of PSG funding from the Qatar Tourism Authority was inflated.
