Difficulties arose in obtaining an international driver&#39;s license in Russia
Traffic police units are experiencing a shortage of international driving licenses (IDPs).
To get such a license, you have to wait in line for several weeks, which has become a real problem for vacationers who want to go on vacation abroad in their own car or rent it there.
It is worth noting that the situation with international driving licenses remains controversial.
The IDP was introduced to make it easier for the foreign police to understand what is written in the national identity card, since the information in it is explained in five languages.
The requirements for international rights are recorded in the 1968 Vienna Convention on Road Traffic, but in the countries that have ratified the Vienna Convention, Russian rights are recognized this way.
However, in reality, everything depends on the specific police officers or the rental office: some require an IDP, and some require national rights.
To be on the safe side, drivers still receive international rights, but it should be borne in mind that in countries that have not ratified the convention (for example, the USA, Spain, Mexico, Indonesia), the authorities have the right not to recognize either national rights or IDPs.
Now there is a problem with the forms in almost all departments of the traffic police, reports &quot;Kommersant&quot;, having conducted a study in a number of regions.
So, in Moscow, in the UGIBDD divisions, coupons are simply not issued, the forms have not been enough for four months.
You can make an appointment on the public services website, but there the line has already stretched out until mid-August.
