You need to get international license very urgently.
In Moscow, all the time it is hammered far ahead, on the spot, coupons are not issued at all (there is a button, but the coupon cannot be given).
It seems that the portal of state services shows that in St. Petersburg there is a fig of free time.
Has anyone tried getting in another city?
Will it work?
As explained in the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation, the requirements for the forms of international driver&#39;s licenses have changed, so new forms are being supplied to the departments of the State Traffic Inspectorate.
The deficit may be associated with this, however, it is not clear what changes are in question, previously this was not reported.
The forms are purchased by the Center for Special Purpose in the Field of Road Safety (CSN BDD) of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation and then delivers them to the traffic police departments.
In recent years, all contracts were concluded with Goznak: in 2014-2015, almost 200 thousand IDP forms were produced, in 2016 15 thousand forms were purchased, in 2017 - 90 thousand, but the last contract was signed 18 July with LLC &quot;First Printing House&quot; for the production of 70 thousand forms.
There is a version that the CSN simply did not have time to hold the tender on time, which is why there was a shortage.
However, there are other versions of the lack of forms: because of the crisis, many people began to travel independently not to Europe, but to cheaper Asian countries - China, Thailand, and so on.
